# Keep the build context small & fast — these are never needed inside images.
# NOTE: the build CONTEXT is the repo root for all three services (see
# docker-compose.yml `context: .`), so THIS file governs every build. Per-service
# .dockerignore files would be ignored, so we keep one authoritative list here.

# Dependencies & build outputs (installed/produced inside the image instead)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/.vercel

# VCS & editor
.git
.gitignore
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# Secrets & local env (NEXT_PUBLIC_* arrive as build args; runtime env via compose)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Test/coverage & lint caches
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/.eslintcache

# Logs & OS cruft
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Docs & misc that never affect a build
docs
scripts/*.md
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.local
